comment.author: 47201412@N02
comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/state-records-nsw] I think you missed [http://www.flickr.com/photos/51487922@N05]'s ID guys! The architectural details match up exactly. [http://www.flickr.com/photos/state-records-nsw/2795397054/]The court house and tower was designed by NSW Government Architect Walter Liberty Vernon, and was built between 1895-1896, and as the photo shows it is still a construction site, this dates the photo to this period. NSW Heritage Branch listing - www.environment.nsw.gov.au/heritageapp/ViewHeritageItemDe...
